    <selectionEntry id="712a-2a86-1e9d-3a18" name="Goaded Great Knarloc Herd (IA)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" field="hidden" value="true">
          <conditions>
            <condition field="selections" scope="force" value="1.0" percentValue="false" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true" includeChildForces="false" childId="3261-6601-5bfe-f5d0" type="equalTo"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <rules>
        <rule id="2cc9-097e-a4d1-9e5b" name="Greater Knarloc Goads" hidden="false">
          <description>The Great Knarloc is far larger than its goads and is more likely to be hit by incoming fire. Randomize any hits on the squad by rolling a D6. 1-3 the shots hit the Kroot Goads, 4-6 hits the Great Knarloc.
If all the Goads are killed then the Knarloc must make a leadership test. If it passes it is enraged enough to fight on as nromal, if it fails the Great Knarloc flees the battlefield, remove it from play.
A Great Knarloc with no remaining Goads cannot capture table quarters, hold objectives or count as scoring units.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="8e28-7399-34de-3603" name="Feeding Frenzy" hidden="false">
          <description>If a Great Knarloc rolls more 1s than 6s in close combat it gets carried away and eats one of its Goads. Immediately remove the closest Goad in the unit from play.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="bdfa-03bf-17ee-c2e8" name="Signature Evolutionary Adaptations" hidden="false">
          <description>The Great Knarloc is not affected by signature evolutionary adaptations. The Goads and Shaper must take the same adaptation as the rest of the army.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="480d-437b-98a0-9150" name="Fieldcraft" hidden="false">
          <description>Kroot gain +1 to their cover save in woods or jungles. Kroot in woods or jungles do not roll a Difficult Terrain test; they may always move up to 6&quot;. If they do not move in the movement phase they may see and shoot through 12&quot; of woods or jungle terrain rather than the normal 6&quot;</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
      <infoLinks>
        <infoLink id="cb21-b0e9-7996-5589" name="Great Knarloc" hidden="false" targetId="5ed5-bc58-9aad-49ec" type="profile"/>
        <infoLink id="2f07-b592-ae23-f81e" name="Rending" hidden="false" targetId="0869-c2b5-1933-775b" type="rule"/>
        <infoLink id="8c3e-5293-36f9-c089" name="Fleet of Foot" hidden="false" targetId="6f0a-684d-7a67-2dd6" type="rule">
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" field="name" value="Hyperactive Nymune Organ"/>
          </modifiers>
        </infoLink>
      </infoLinks>
