    <selectionEntry id="fb2e-5d75-8b2d-dc54" name="Knarloc Rider Herd (IA)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" field="hidden" value="true">
          <conditions>
            <condition field="selections" scope="force" value="1.0" percentValue="false" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true" includeChildForces="false" childId="3261-6601-5bfe-f5d0" type="equalTo"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <rules>
        <rule id="5c72-73ab-8e82-b299" name="Signature Evolutionary Adaptations" hidden="false">
          <description>The Knarloc is not affected by signature evolutionary adaptations.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="d1ce-6061-3f87-9c21" name="Fieldcraft" hidden="false">
          <description>Kroot gain +1 to their cover save in woods or jungles. Kroot in woods or jungles do not roll a Difficult Terrain test; they may always move up to 6&quot;. If they do not move in the movement phase they may see and shoot through 12&quot; of woods or jungle terrain rather than the normal 6&quot;</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="d6b6-52b7-d362-94ef" name="Eaters of the Dead" hidden="false">
          <description>Kroot must pass a Leadership test in order to pursue a foe defeated in close combat or make a sweeping advance. If the test is failed the Kroot must instead consolidate. If a Kroot Shaper is in the squad then they MUST consolidate, they have no choice.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
      <infoLinks>
        <infoLink id="ee36-b894-3edc-3acc" name="Cavalry" hidden="false" targetId="0e80-1d1e-f91a-11fe" type="rule"/>
        <infoLink id="f688-f212-47bc-f6e0" name="Fleet of Foot" hidden="false" targetId="6f0a-684d-7a67-2dd6" type="rule">
