  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="tau0-299b-863e-1fb1" name="Recoil Absorption" hidden="false">
      <description>All XV battlesuits are designed to compensate for the recoil of light weapons fire, so they do not count as moving when they fire rapid fire weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-e040-2ca5-aa59" name="Improved Sensors" hidden="false">
      <description>Crisis, Stealth, and Broadside battlesuits are equipped with a number of variable spectrum sensors and scanners. These sensors allow them to detech ambushes or Lictors using secret deployment. One member of the team may scan instead of shooting during the Shooting phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-ec6a-0dcb-d81f" name="Jetpack" hidden="false">
      <description>Tau jetpacks are extremely agile, combining anti-gravitic and jet technology. A model with a jetpack can either:
- Move 6&quot; in their Movement phase, ignoring intervening terrain as they fly over it like a model with a jump pack;
- Move up to 6&quot; by walking or hovering just above the ground as normal infantry.
They will also fall back and sweeping advance 3D6&quot;.
Troops equipped with jetpacks may Deep Strike when the mission permits.
An unbroken model with a jetpack that is not in close combat may always move 6&quot; in the Assault phase whether they are with 6&quot; of an enemy or not. This move may be in any direction. It does not have to be a charge towards the enemy, even if the jetpack wearer is within 6&quot; of an enemy model.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-d934-3cfb-7a6a" name="Stealthsuit" hidden="false">
      <description>Strealthsuits incorporate a holographic disruption field that makes it wearer hard to spot. Enemy models attempting to fire at Stealth armor troops count as if firing at night and must roll to check their spotting distance. If the Stealthsuit troopers are not within spotting range the unit misses its chance to fire while searching for a target and so may not choose a different target. Stealthsuit troopers count as being in cover if they are assaulted, but not if they charge. If firing at Stealthsuits while the Night Fighting scenario special rules are in effect, the rolled spotting distance is halved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-4fc4-3974-c586" name="Multi-tracker" hidden="false">
      <description>Enabled the wearer to fire two weapon systems at the same time.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-5621-8ff1-e373" name="Shield Generator" hidden="false">
      <description>This confers a 4+ Invulnerable save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-a13f-c004-e8dd" name="Drone Controller" hidden="false">
      <description>A drone controller enables the suit wearer to command from 1 to 2 gun or sheild drones.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-2d35-c5f7-9db4" name="Bonding Knife" hidden="false">
      <description>A bonded team may regroup even if below half strength. </description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-cfd0-1939-ad50" name="Blacksun Filter" hidden="false">
      <description>Enables the user to see up to 4D6 x 3&quot; when fighting at night.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-f290-815c-7312" name="Decoy Launchers" hidden="false">
      <description>Whenever a Glancing Hit result of 4 (Immobilised) is rolled against the vehicle, the decoy launchers force the damage dice to be re-rolled, but the re-rolled result stands.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-21e2-5667-f96d" name="Disruption Pod" hidden="false">
      <description>Weapons firing at a vehicle equiped with a Disruption Pod reduce their range by 6&quot;, down to a minimum of 24&quot; or the maximum range of the weapon, whichever is less.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-2fa4-d273-0725" name="Flechette Discharger" hidden="false">
      <description>If an enemy model elects to make a death or glory attempt during a tank shock by a vehicle equipped with flechette dischargers, it must first pass an Armour saving throw or suffer one wound.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-d1a8-b8ae-b4ad" name="Seeker Missiles" hidden="false">
      <description>Any model equipped with a markerlight may request a single missile to be launched if they score a hit on the desired target with their markerlight. The missles do not need a line of sight from the vehicle to the target, and they hit on a 2+. Against vehicles, the missle strikes the armour facing the firing vehicle, even if the markerlight is in a different facing. The target can still use the benefits of cover they are in or immediately behind.
The vehicle equipped with the missiles cannot launch them itself. They are always fired by other models armed with markerlights.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-db84-ec11-bf2c" name="Sensor Spines" hidden="false">
      <description>Sensor spines allow the vehicle to detect ambushes (Codex: Catachans, p.20) and secret deployments (Lictors, Codex: Tyranids, p.11). They may shoot and scan in the same Shooting Phase. Additionally, a vehicle fitted with sensor spines will only trigger a mine when passing over a minefield on a roll of 6.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-f6e9-89c3-4bf3" name="Target Lock" hidden="false">
      <description>Target Lock enables the model to target a separate enemy unit to that engaged by the rest of its own unit.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-d3df-81a4-b045" name="Targeting Array" hidden="false">
      <description>Add +1 BS to the model (Up to BS 5).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-8efb-924c-cc99" name="Vectored Retro-thrusters" hidden="false">
      <description>Models with this ability may choose to leave close combat. Declare this at the end of the Close Combat phase. The unit must be involved in combat, and will immediately move 3D6&quot; in a straight line in any direction, ignoring the units they are locked with. This move may not be used to move into contact with any enemy models. The break-off move is automatically successful and is not subject to sweeping advance The enemy can consolidate normally, however. If accompanied by drones, using Vectored Retro-thrusters will abandon the drones which are automatically destroyed.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-f92c-58fd-ccb7" name="Advanced Stabilisation System" hidden="false">
      <description>During the movement phase the battlesuit may choose to move as in difficult terrain for the remainder of the turn, though if it does it may not make an additional jetpack move in the assault phase. This allows it to fire heavy weapon as if it was stationary that turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-5fc1-a9d5-0fe8" name="Command &amp; Control Node" hidden="false">
      <description>A sophisticated AI-assisted transmission system. All friendly units with a model within 12&quot; may use the bearer&apos;s Leadership.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-978f-4c93-a358" name="Positional Relay" hidden="false">
      <description>This records detailed battlefield data and relays it in a tight-band, encrypted burst to a single unit operating as a strategic reserve. From the second turn onwards, as long as the bearer is on the table at the beginning of the turn in which this device is used, a single unit that is being held in Reserve may be deployed on a D6 roll of 2+, though no other units in Reserve may be deployed this turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-54a8-7787-30ac" name="Ejection System" hidden="false">
      <description>This system provides the pilot a chance of escaping catastrophic damage to his battlesuit. Should the character lose his last wound to a shooting attack that does not cause Instant Death, the battlesuit is replaced with a single model, representing the pilot equipped with a Pulse Pistol. Sha&apos;o or Shas&apos;el only.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-fc58-e09f-c788" name="Failsafe Detonator" hidden="false">
      <description>This device is intended as the ultimate expression of the doctrine of the Greater Good, and is to be used only in the direst of circumstances. The failsafe detonator may be triggered if the bearer is part of a team that is forced to make a Fall Back move having lost an assault.
The team is moved as normal, but the character says where he is and the enemy may not make a Sweeping Advance. Once his team has moved, and before Pile in moves, the character activates the detonator -- place the Large Blast marker centred on the character, and roll for partial hits on other models as normal.
Every model hit takes a single, Strength 8, AP- hit, and the character is removed as a casualty. The enemy may not Consolidate.
Note that the enemy unit need not take a Morale check should this attack inflict 25% casualties, as it occurs outside the normal sequence in which such checks are required.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-a35c-4984-d679" name="Stimulant Injector" hidden="false">
      <description>The character&apos;s battlesuit is fitted with an advanced life support system that is able to flood his system with stimulants should he become wounded.
If he lose a wound roll a dice; on a 3 or less the wound is taken as normal, on a 4 or more the wound is ignored and the model continues fighting. This ability cannot be used against weapons whose strength is at least twice the Toughness of the model being hit or against close combat weapons that allow no save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-914c-4e8c-1ca6" name="Networked Markerlight" hidden="false">
      <description>A networked markerlight is a specialised version of the standard system, but it is larger and less common. Unlike a normal markerlight, the operator&apos;s own unit may benefit from its use. It is fired before the remainder of the unit fires. All other rules given for the basic markerlight apply.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-cb03-d305-2364" name="Close Protection" hidden="false">
      <description>Shield Drones always have the same Toughness and Armour Save values as the individual they accompany.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-1e7e-493e-962d" name="Advanced Shield Generator" hidden="false">
      <description>This confers a 4+ Invulnerable save against shooting and a 3+ Invulnerable save in close combat.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-7a78-e627-fb10" name="Advanced Target Lock" hidden="false">
      <description>Target Lock enables the model to target a separate enemy unit to that engaged by the rest of its own unit and target a separate enemy unit with each weapon, if desired.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-7078-8772-e0ba" name="Multi-tracker &amp; Stabilisation System" hidden="false">
      <description>Enables the vehicle to fire as if it were a fast vehicle. Therefore it can fire one weapon if moving up to 12&quot; and all weapons if moving up to 6&quot;.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-31eb-04d6-c113" name="Iridium Armour Plates" hidden="false">
      <description>The character&apos;s battlesuit is fitted with additional armour protection, in the form of iridium armour plates fitted across its surface.
These increase the model&apos;s Armour Save to 2+, but the additional 6&quot; move in the Assault phase is reduced to D6&quot;.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-42a7-2c4a-a281" name="Stealth Field Generator" hidden="false">
      <description>Enemy models attempting to fire at a model equipped with Stealth Field Generator count as if firing at night and must roll to check their spotting distance. If the model is not within spotting range the unit misses its chance to fire while searching for a target and so may not choose a different target. Models equipped with Stealth Field Generator count as being in cover if they are assaulted, but not if they charge. If firing at a model equipped with Stealth Field Generator while the Night Fighting scenario special rules are in effect, the rolled spotting distance is halved.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="tau0-aac8-3daa-b867" name="Acute Senses" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="tau0-be8a-8bae-1dcd" name="Special Character" hidden="false">
      <description>May only be used in Tau armies of at least 1,500 points.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
  <sharedProfiles>
